This paper deals with image generation and deep network architectures, which are primarily studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories of arXiv CS. The paper also involves learning to disentangle attributes and apply desired attribute changes, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with image retrieval experiments, which are commonly studied in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training a convolutional network, which is a type of neural network, and thus falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
